functional interfaces
---------------------
	- interfaces which have only one abstract method
	- can have any number of default and static methods and variables
	- also known by name SAM(Single Abstract Method) interfaces. Eg: Runnable, Comparable
	- we can annotate them with @FunctionalInterface annotation

3 ways to provide implementation for a functional interface
-----------------------------------------------------------
first way - conventional way 
second way - anonymous classes
third way - lambda expressions


4 basic in-built functional interfaces given by java
-----------------------------------------------------
Function
Consumer
Predicate
Supplier
